# SYS-LIC-GATE-Z3
## DeadLetter & Operations Alert Controller

Version: 2.0

---

# Overview

SYS-LIC-GATE-Z3 serves as the terminal exception controller for the HyperSync License Operating System.

When replay recovery has been exhausted or a license operation reaches an unrecoverable state, Gate Z3 assumes ownership of the execution. Rather than attempting additional processing, it classifies the failure, generates operational intelligence, records immutable governance evidence, and notifies the operations team through deterministic alert workflows.

Gate Z3 functions as the final safety boundary protecting the License Operating System from silent failures while providing complete operational visibility.

---

# Architectural Purpose

Gate Z3 is responsible for:

• DeadLetter Detection

• Failure Classification

• Operational Severity Analysis

• Alert Deduplication

• Operations Notification

• DeadLetter Queue Management

• Immutable Governance Evidence

---

# Core Responsibilities

The controller performs the following operational sequence:

- Detect DeadLetter events
- Validate operational eligibility
- Classify failure severity
- Generate deterministic alert payloads
- Prevent duplicate notifications
- Record DeadLetter operational state
- Append immutable governance evidence
- Notify Operations via Slack
- Finalize operational status

Each failure is processed once using deterministic alert contracts.

