# Alert Severity Model

Gate Z3 categorizes failures using operational severity levels.

Severity Levels

• Low

• Medium

• High

• Critical

Only High and Critical events generate immediate operational notifications.

Lower severity events remain fully governed while avoiding unnecessary operational noise.

---

# DeadLetter Management

Each unrecoverable replay is committed to the operational DeadLetter Queue.

Operational state includes:

- DeadLetter_ID
- Replay_ID
- Correlation_ID
- License_ID
- Failure_Category
- Failure_Reason
- Alert_Severity
- Processing_Status
- Notification_Status
- Replay_Attempts

The DeadLetter Queue serves as the authoritative operational source for unresolved execution failures.

